ernational goals===\n:''As of match played 17 November 2019. England score listed first, score column indicates score after each Sterling goal.''<ref name=NFT/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|+ International goals by date, venue, cap, opponent, score, result and competition\n|-\n!scope=col|No.\n!scope=col|Date\n!scope=col|Venue\n!scope=col|Cap\n!scope=col|Opponent\n!scope=col|Score\n!scope=col|Result\n!scope=col|Competition\n!scope=col class=unsortable|{{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n!scope=row style=text-align:center|1\n|27 March 2015||[[Wembley Stadium]], London, England||align=center|14||{{fb|LTU}}||align=center|3\u20130||align=center|4\u20130||[[UEFA Euro 2016 qualification]]||align=center|<ref name=\"England 4\u20130 Lithuania\"/>\n|-\n!scope=row style=text-align:center|2\n|9 October 2015||[[Wembley Stadium]], London, England||align=center|18||{{fb|EST}}||align=center|2\u20130||align=center|2\u20130||[[UEFA Euro 2016 qualification]]||align=center|<ref name=\"England 2\u20130 Estonia\"/>\n|-\n!scope=row style=text-align:center|3\n|rowspan=2|15 October 2018||rowspan=2|[[Estadio Benito Villamar\u00edn]], Seville, Spain||rowspan=2 align=center|46||rowspan=2|{{fb|ESP}}||align=center|1\u20130||rowspan=2 align=center|3\u20132||rowspan=2|[[2018\u201319 UEFA Nations League A]]||rowspan=2 align=center|<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45780621 |title=Spain 2\u20133 England |first=Phil |last=McNulty |website=BBC Sport |date=15 October 2018 |accessdate=15 October 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row style=text-align:center|4\n|align=center|3\u20130\n|-\n!scope=row style=text-align:center|5\n|rowspan=3|22 March 2019||rowspan=3|[[Wembley Stadium]], London, England||rowspan=3 align=center|48||rowspan=3|{{fb|CZE}}||align=center|1\u20130||rowspan=3 align=center|5\u20130||rowspan=3|[[UEFA Euro 2020 qualification]]||rowspan=3 align=center|<ref name=Czech/>\n|-\n!scope=row style=text-align:center|6\n|align=center|3\u20130\n|-\n!scope=row style=t