ocial groups of Maharashtra]]\n[[Category:Scheduled Castes of Delhi]]\n[[Category:Scheduled Tribes of India]]\n[[Category:Denotified tribes of India]]\n[[Category:Scheduled Castes of Madhya Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Agriculturalists]] \n[[Category:Agricultural castes]]\n[[Category:Social groups of India]] \n[[Category:Social groups of Rajasthan]] \n[[Category:Social groups of Jammu and Kashmir]] \n[[Category:Social groups of Haryana]] \n[[Category:Social groups of Himachal Pradesh]] \n[[Category:Social groups of Karnataka]]\n[[Category:Pirates]] \n[[Category:Pirates by nationality]] \n[[Category:Indian caste system]] \n[[Category:Indian people]]\n[[Category:Hindu surnames]] \n[[Category:Indian family names]]\n[[Category:Koli princely states]] \n[[Category:Koli people]]\n[[Category:Ethnic groups in India]] \n[[Category:Ethnic groups in India by state or union territory]]\n", "name_user": "PawanjiGupta", "label": "safe", "comment": "Merged theThakorsubcaste of kolis in this page", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Koli_people"}
{"title_page": "Earth Run", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name = Earth Run\n| type = studio\n| artist = [[Lee Ritenour]]\n| cover = Lee Ritenour - Earth Run.jpg\n| released = April 1986\n| recorded = \n| studio = Starlight Studio, [[Burbank, California]]\n| genre = [[Jazz fusion]]\n| length = 44:28\n| label = [[GRP Records|GRP]]\n| producer  = {{hlist|Lee Ritenour|Greg Mathieson|[[Dave Grusin]]|[[Larry Rosen (producer)|Larry Rosen]]}}\n| prev_title = [[Harlequin (album)|Harlequin]]\n| prev_year = 1985\n| next_title = [[Portrait (Lee Ritenour album)|Portrait]]\n| next_year = 1987\n}}\n\n'''''Earth Run''''' is the fifteenth studio album by [[jazz]] guitarist [[Lee Ritenour]], released in April 1986 through [[GRP Records]].<ref name=allmusic>[https://www.allmusic.com/album/earth-run-mw0000192397 \"Earth Run - Lee Ritenour\"]. ''[[AllMusic]]''. [[RhythmOne]]. Retrieved February 16, 2020.</ref> The album reached number ten on the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' Jazz Albums chart in the United States<ref name=Album>{{cite work|title=Lee Ritenour: Earth Run|date=April 1986|publisher=GRP Records}}</ref><ref name=BBD>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/lee-ritenour/chart-history/JLP/song/325321|title=Lee Ritenour: Earth Run (Jazz Albums)|publisher=Billboard Magazine|website=billboard.com}}</ref> and received a [[Grammy Award]] nomination for [[Grammy Award for Best Jazz Fusion Performance|Best jazz fusion performance, vocal or instrumental]]. The title track was also nominated for [[Grammy Award for Best Instrumental Composition|Best Instrumental Composition]].<ref name=grammy>{{cite web|url=https://www.grammy.com/grammys/artists/lee-ritenour|title=Lee Ritenour|website=Grammy.com}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1score = {{Rating|2.5|5}}<ref name=allmusic/>\n}}\n\nRichard S. Ginell at [[AllMusic]] awarded ''Earth Run'' 2.5 stars out of 5, calling it \"a more interesting record than most of its immediate predecessors\" and noting the \"peculiarly fuzzy, futuristic sound\" of Ritenour's [[SynthAxe]] guitar synthesizer (one of nine different guitars used on the album). He also listed \"The Sauce\" and the cover of [[Herbie Hancock]]'s \"Butterfly\" as highlights.\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| title1 = Soaring\n| writer1 = Lee Ritenour\n| length1 = 5:38\n| title2 = Earth Run\n| writer2 = Ritenour, [[Dave Grusin]]\n| length2 = 4:39\n| title3 = If I'm Dreamin' (Don't Wake Me)\n| writer3 = Ritenour, [[Martin Page]], [[Maurice White]]\n| length3 = 5:12\n| title4 = Watercolors\n| writer4 = [[Don Grusin]]\n| length4 = 5:14\n| title5 = The Sauce\n| writer5 = Greg Mathieson\n| length5 = 4:22\n| title6 = Butterfly\n| writer6 = [[Herbie Hancock]]\n| length6 = 5:11\n| title7 = Hero\n| note7 = CD edition bonus track\n| writer7 = Ritenour, Grusin\n| length7 = 3:52\n| title8 = Sanctuary\n| writer8 = Ritenour\n| length8 = 4:46\n| title9 = Water from the Moon\n| writer9 = Ritenour\n| length9 = 5:33\n| total_length = 44:28\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n{{div col}}\n*Lee Ritenour \u2013 guitar, [[SynthAxe]], [[arrangement]] (tracks 1\u20133, 5\u20139), production\n*[[Phil Perry]] \u2013 lead vocals (track 3)\n*[[Maurice White]] \u2013 vocals (track 3)\n*[[Tommy Funderburk]] \u2013 vocals (track 3)\n*[[Ernie Watts]] \u2013 tenor saxophone\n*[[Tom Scott (musician)|Tom Scott]] \u2013 [[Lyricon]]\n*[[Larry Williams (jazz musician)|Larry Williams]] \u2013 SynthAxe programming (tracks 1, 2), synthesizer programming (track 3)\n*[[Dave Grusin]] \u2013 keyboard (tracks 1, 2, 4, 6, 9), piano, arrangement (tracks 2, 4, 7, 9), executive production\n*[[Don Grusin]] \u2013 keyboard (track 7), synthesizer (track 4)\n*Greg Mathieson \u2013 keyboard (track 5), bass synthesizer (track 5), arrangement (track 5), producer\n*[[David Foster]] \u2013 keyboard (track 3), bass synthesizer, (track 3), arrangment (track 3)\n*[[Carlos Vega]] \u2013 drums (tracks 1\u20133, 5\u20137, 9)\n*[[Harvey Mason]] \u2013 drums (track 8)\n*[[Paulinho da Costa]] \u2013 percussion\n*[[Jimmy Johnson (bassist)|Jimmy Johnson]] \u2013 bass (tracks 1, 4, 7, 9)\n*[[Abraham Laboriel]] \u2013 bass (tracks 2, 6)\n*Marcus Ryle \u2013 SynthAxe programming (tracks 1, 2), synthesizer programming (track 7)\n*Casey Young \u2013 synthesizer programming (track 5)\n*Jerry Hey \u2013 horn arrangment (track 1)\n*Larry Rosen \u2013 executive production\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Chart (1986)\n! Peak<br>position\n|-\n| ''[[Billboard charts|Billboard]]'' Jazz Albums<ref name=BBD />\n| align=center| 10\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://leeritenour.com/cds/earth-run/ Earth Run] at Lee Ritenour's official site\n\n{{Lee Ritenour}}\n\n[[Category:1986 albums]]\n[[Category:GRP Records albums]]\n[[Category:Lee Ritenour albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Dave Grusin]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name = Earth Run\n| type = studio\n| artist = [[Lee Ritenour]]\n| cover = Lee Ritenour - Earth Run.jpg\n| released = April 1986\n| recorded = \n| studio = Starlight Studio, [[Burbank, California]]\n| genre = [[Jazz fusion]]\n| length = 44:28\n| label = [[GRP Records|GRP]]\n| producer  = {{hlist|Lee Ritenour|Greg Mathieson|[[Dave Grusin]]|[[Larry Rosen (producer)|Larry Rosen]]}}\n| prev_title = [[Harlequin (album)|Harlequin]]\n| prev_year = 1985\n| next_title = [[Portrait (Lee Ritenour album)|Portrait]]\n| next_year = 1987\n}}\n\n'''''Earth Run''''' is the fifteenth studio album by [[jazz]] guitarist [[Lee Ritenour]], released in April 1986 through [[GRP Records]].<ref name=allmusic>[https://www.allmusic.com/album/earth-run-mw0000192397 \"Earth Run - Lee Ritenour\"]. ''[[AllMusic]]''. [[RhythmOne]]. Retrieved February 16, 2020.</ref> The album reached number ten on the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' Jazz Albums chart in the United States,<ref name=Album>{{cite work|title=Lee Ritenour: Earth Run|date=April 1986|publisher=GRP Records}}</ref><ref name=BBD>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/lee-ritenour/chart-history/JLP/song/325321|title=Lee Ritenour: Earth Run (Jazz Albums)|publisher=Billboard Magazine|website=billboard.com}}</ref> and received a [[Grammy Award]] nomination for [[Grammy Award for Best Jazz Fusion Performance|Best jazz fusion performance, vocal or instrumental]]. The title track was also nominated for [[Grammy Award for Best Instrumental Composition|Best Instrumental Composition]].<ref name=grammy>{{cite web|url=https://www.grammy.com/grammys/artists/lee-ritenour|title=Lee Ritenour|website=Grammy.com}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1score = {{Rating|2.5|5}}<ref name=allmusic/>\n}}\n\nRichard S. Ginell at [[AllMusic]] awarded ''Earth Run'' 2.5 stars out of 5, calling it \"a more interesting record than most of its immediate predecessors\" and noting the \"peculiarly fuzzy, futuristic sound\" of Ritenour's [[SynthAxe]] guitar synthesizer (one of nine different guitars used on the album). He also listed \"The Sauce\" and the cover of [[Herbie Hancock]]'s \"Butterfly\" as highlights.\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| title1 = Soaring\n| writer1 = Lee Ritenour\n| length1 = 5:38\n| title2 = Earth Run\n| writer2 = Ritenour, [[Dave Grusin]]\n| length2 = 4:39\n| title3 = If I'm Dreamin' (Don't Wake Me)\n| writer3 = Ritenour, [[Martin Page]], [[Maurice White]]\n| length3 = 5:12\n| title4 = Watercolors\n| writer4 = [[Don Grusin]]\n| length4 = 5:14\n| title5 = The Sauce\n| writer5 = Greg Mathieson\n| length5 = 4:22\n| title6 = Butterfly\n| writer6 = [[Herbie Hancock]]\n| length6 = 5:11\n| title7 = Hero\n| note7 = CD edition bonus track\n| writer7 = Ritenour, Grusin\n| length7 = 3:52\n| title8 = Sanctuary\n| writer8 = Ritenour\n| length8 = 4:46\n| title9 = Water from the Moon\n| writer9 = Ritenour\n| length9 = 5:33\n| total_length = 44:28\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n{{div col}}\n*Lee Ritenour \u2013 guitar, [[SynthAxe]], [[arrangement]] (tracks 1\u20133, 5\u20139), production\n*[[Phil Perry]] \u2013 lead vocals (track 3)\n*[[Maurice White]] \u2013 vocals (track 3)\n*[[Tommy Funderburk]] \u2013 vocals (track 3)\n*[[Ernie Watts]] \u2013 tenor saxophone\n*[[Tom Scott (musician)|Tom Scott]] \u2013 [[Lyricon]]\n*[[Larry Williams (jazz musician)|Larry Williams]] \u2013 SynthAxe programming (tracks 1, 2), synthesizer programming (track 3)\n*[[Dave Grusin]] \u2013 keyboard (tracks 1, 2, 4, 6, 9), piano, arrangement (tracks 2, 4, 7, 9), executive production\n*[[Don Grusin]] \u2013 keyboard (track 7), synthesizer (track 4)\n*Greg Mathieson \u2013 keyboard (track 5), bass synthesizer (track 5), arrangement (track 5), producer\n*[[David Foster]] \u2013 keyboard (track 3), bass synthesizer, (track 3), arrangment (track 3)\n*[[Carlos Vega]] \u2013 drums (tracks 1\u20133, 5\u20137, 9)\n*[[Harvey Mason]] \u2013 drums (track 8)\n*[[Paulinho da Costa]] \u2013 percussion\n*[[Jimmy Johnson (bassist)|Jimmy Johnson]] \u2013 bass (tracks 1, 4, 7, 9)\n*[[Abraham Laboriel]] \u2013 bass (tracks 2, 6)\n*Marcus Ryle \u2013 SynthAxe programming (tracks 1, 2), synthesizer programming (track 7)\n*Casey Young \u2013 synthesizer programming (track 5)\n*Jerry Hey \u2013 horn arrangment (track 1)\n*Larry Rosen \u2013 executive production\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Chart (1986)\n! Peak<br>position\n|-\n| ''[[Billboard charts|Billboard]]'' Jazz Albums<ref name=BBD />\n| align=center| 10\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://leeritenour.com/cds/earth-run/ Earth Run] at Lee Ritenour's official site\n\n{{Lee Ritenour}}\n\n[[Category:1986 albums]]\n[[Category:GRP Records albums]]\n[[Category:Lee Ritenour albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Dave Grusin]]\n", "name_user": "Mac Dreamstate", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Earth_Run"}
